8.11	American_philosopher	American philosophy	American philosophy is the philosophical activity or output of Americans, both within the United States and abroad. The Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy notes that while American philosophy lacks a "core of defining features, American Philosophy can nevertheless be seen as both reflecting and shaping collective American identity over the history of the nation."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Scene_at_the_Signing_of_the_Constitution_of_the_United_States.png/320px-Scene_at_the_Signing_of_the_Constitution_of_the_United_States.png.jpeg
